FT  14 SEP 94 / UK Company News: BDM climbs 15%
British Data Management, the specialist data management and storage group,
raised pre-tax profits by 15 per cent from a restated Pounds 4.01m to Pounds
4.62m for the year ended June 30. Turnover was ahead 8 per cent at Pounds
16.8m.
Interest charges took an increased Pounds 705,000 (Pounds 224,000) as a
result of acquiring two properties previously leased. Earnings per share
were 14.1p (restated 13.4p) and a final dividend of 3.75p makes a total of
5.4p (4.75p).
